    {
      "id": 208,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -2520,
        -120
      ],
      "size": [
        820,
        1380
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 9,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n\nAuthor: Sharvin Suntoobacus\n\nYouTube Channel: CodeCraftersCorner\n\nPatreon: [Support on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n---\n\n### ℹ️ About This Workflow\n\nThis workflow allows users to transfer specific clothing items or garments from one image to a target character. By utilizing Flux.2 Klein and automated masking, users can swap outfits, change patterns, or showcase products on human models while maintaining high visual fidelity and texture detail.\n\n### 🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n\n[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/78M0i9v1YOc)\n\n### 📥 Model Links (for Local Users)\n\n**diffusion_models**\n\n* [Flux.2 Klein 9B GGUF](https://huggingface.co/unsloth/FLUX.2-klein-9B-GGUF/tree/main) (Recommended for low VRAM)\n\n**text_encoders**\n\n* t5xxl_fp16.safetensors or clip_l.safetensors\n\n**vae**\n\n* ae.safetensors (Flux VAE)\n\n---\n\n### 📂 Model Storage Location\n\nPlace the downloaded files into the following directories within your ComfyUI installation:\n\n```\n📂 ComfyUI/\n├── 📂 models/\n│   ├── 📂 unet/\n│   │   └── FLUX.2-klein-9B-GGUF.gguf\n│   ├── 📂 text_encoders/\n│   │   └── t5xxl_fp16.safetensors\n│   └── 📂 vae/\n│       └── ae.safetensors\n```\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Notes\n* **GGUF Support:** To use the GGUF version, you must install the **ComfyUI-GGUF** custom node by City96 via the ComfyUI Manager.\n* **Input Images:** Image 1 (Bottom) is the target character; Image 2 (Top) is the source garment.\n* **Masking:** Ensure the prompt in the masking section accurately describes the item (e.g., \"dress\", \"shirt\", \"shoes\") to ensure SAM 3 provides a clean cutout.\n* **Variations:** Set the noise seed to \"randomize\" if you need to generate different fits or hairstyles for the same input.\n\n**Credit:** Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share YouTube Channel Code Crafters Corner when sharing this workflow.\n**Support:** Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!\n\n[YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/@CodeCraftersCorner) | [Patreon Page](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n🙏 **Thank you for your support!**"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
